  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Unity.TextMeshPro::TMPro.TextMeshProUGUI
  m_Material: {fileID: 0}
  m_Color: {r: 1, g: 1, b: 1, a: 1}
  m_RaycastTarget: 1
  m_RaycastPadding: {x: 0, y: 0, z: 0, w: 0}
  m_Maskable: 1
  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: "This is a marketing research to understand about male characters in American
    and China games\r\n\r\nAmerica and China are one of the biggest markets of gaming.
    We would like to analyse how male characters in the games developed by the both
    of them have involved overtime. In America, modern male characters tend to possess
    traits of traditional American masculinity, such as being physically imposing
    and stoic. However, recently, they have also shown more signs of emotional sensitivity.
    Similarly, modern male characters in China possess a more effeminate and softer
    look. To understand this, we look at what contemporary masculinity in these countries
    is like. \r\n\r\nWe also look at how capitalism shaped contemporary masculinity
    in both countries. Out of the many factors, we chose this because of how integrated
    capitalism is in our lives throughout history and how it has played a significant
    role in shaping mankind's taste and preferences\r\n\r\n"
